summary: Sigh I remember in 2016 wondering if anything could ever top the pure excitement I felt while watching the Chicago Cubs kick ass...
body:
Sigh I remember in 2016 wondering if anything could ever top the pure excitement I felt while watching the Chicago Cubs kick ass in the World Series and Bryant hitting yet another grand slam and the venue played “Bad Blood” as everyone ran around to home and everything was just…. great

But this moment… captured with the shaky hands of a Swift Show first-timer losing ALL chill in that moment…

…and then this.

I’m left… speechless? And I don’t think it can be topped? And I’m just holding on so tightly to those memories?!I love you @taylorswift ♥

summary: People aren't just upset about high merch prices, it's largely the fact that Taylor Nation rewards spending large amounts of...
body:
People aren’t just upset about high merch prices, it’s largely the fact that Taylor Nation rewards spending large amounts of money by giving more opportunities to meet/interact with Taylor.

For example: rarely is anybody who isn’t on the floor picked for meet and greet. I understand that it’s hard to pull people out of those crowded places and walk up and down stairs but the spots people are often chosen are the spots that are the most expensive. At the same time, I’m extremely grateful that you don’t need to/can’t buy meet and greets but it’s still kind of hard to watch because it still feels like it’s about who’s willing to pay the most. Another example would be that time Taylor Nation had people post pictures of their merch in order to get invited to Super Saturday Night. It was supposed to be an event for fans - her last show for a long time - but they still had to bring $$ into it. I mean, aren’t travel expenses enough? Come on. A lot of people who were invited to Secret Sessions weren’t even able to afford that.

My point is, I think these opportunities should be given based on how emotionally invested a person is in Taylor cause in the long run, that’s what really matters. @taylornation you guys should know that if we could, we would spend hundreds of dollars on Taylor related things because we love her but the reality is, most of us just can’t and we shouldn’t be overlooked as casual fans because of it.

I hope y'all don’t see us as ungrateful right now, because we really do appreciate all the extra things y'all do for us. Sometimes though…. Sigh.
